  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0baa\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Increase in monthly season ticket charges cannot be accommodated - Railway Station Officials Association",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Increase in railway monthly season ticket fares cannot be allowed to inconvenience the public commuters.",
        "Sumesa Somaratne, President of the Railway Station Officers' Association, said that the increase in season ticket fares due to the new fare revision is unjustified.",
        "He mentioned the above while attending a press conference held today (25) at the office of Railway Station Officers Association in Marudhanai.",
        "The Railway Department has not initially prepared the new fare revision for proper procedures.",
        "The shortfall was pointed out during a meeting held yesterday with the Secretary of the Ministry of Transport following the strike.",
        "Only the normal ticket fares of the train services have been hiked from today in view of the fuel price hike. The minimum fee is fixed at Rs.20.",
        "However, the monthly season ticket fees will be increased manifold. For example, the season fee which is currently Rs 2,980 will be fixed at Rs 6,000 from next month.",
        "Such an unreasonable increase in the monthly season ticket fee can never be accepted.",
        "After the increase in bus fare, most people have started using the train service. He said that if the railway fare is increased in such a situation, the public passengers will face great inconvenience."
      ],
